FT  19 DEC 92 / Letter: Too staid for coded clue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From R E HURST
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Until I saw the letters column of December 15 I had innocently assumed
that David Cannadine's article ('The Royal dilemma that won't go away',
December 12) was a leg pull by your admirable crossword editor.
It seemed to be a coded clue: Contributor is one canned and avid colonial
(5,9) - (David Cannadine).
As a reader of 50 years' standing I should have realised you are much too
staid to include first year undergraduate humour; at least by intention,
even if execution goes awry every decade or so.
R E Hurst,
20 Esk Gardens,
Wetherby, W Yorkshire
