restructuring.
Alcoa, in common with many other US companies, is adopting Financial
Accounting Standard (FAS) 106 and FAS 109 ahead of the first-quarter 1993
deadline.
Charges of about Dollars 1.183bn, or Dollars 13.85, for the adoption of FAS
106 will apply to the years before 1992.
Alcoa also announced 1,100 redundancies as part of a redesign of some
manufacturing and administrative processes.
