<HEADLINE>
FT  18 DEC 92 / World Commodities Prices: Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GOLD held above Dollars 338 a troy ounce on the London bullion market as
option-writers battled to defend positions. 'A lot of Dollars 340 calls are
written for the year's end. Therefore if we break above Dollars 340 a lot of
people would be forced to cover their short positions on options,' one
dealer said. Players defending their positions were selling to keep the
price down. Two big US commission houses might be forced to cover large
short positions if the price rises. A break above Dollars 340 was seen,
taking gold to Dollars 342 and possibly Dollars 344 to Dollars 345. On the
LME trading in base metals was mostly routine as the market wound down in
interest ahead of the holiday season. Three-month COPPER was effectively
stalled below Dollars 2,230 a tonne; three-month ALUMINIUM'S attempt to test
overhead resistance above Dollars 1,250 a tonne ran out of steam; and ZINC
failed to follow through Wednesday's gains. In Chicago WHEAT was mostly
lower by midday on commercial house selling after Russia missed another
payment.
Compiled from Reuters
</TEXT>
