plan during the week of January 11.
The Ontario Securities Commission halted trading in CDollars 325m of bonds
secured on First Canadian Place, O&amp;Y's biggest Canadian property.
O&amp;Y failed to meet a deadline for filing First Canadian's financial
statements. The company said it would do so within the next few days. The
delay was due to the effort required to put together the detailed
restructuring plan.
