FT  18 DEC 92 / International Company News: Gota Bank's shares worthless,
says S-E Banken
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SKANDINAVISKA Enskilda Banken, Sweden's leading commercial bank, said
yesterday that shares in Gota Bank, the country's fourth largest, were
worthless, improving prospects for Gota's reconstruction.
S-E Banken made its gesture conditional on the administrator of Gota AB, the
holding group which collapsed in September, handing the shares over to the
state.
Five years ago, S-E Banken lent SKr1.1bn to Gota AB in return for all Gota
Bank's shares as collateral. S-E Banken stressed it still hoped to get back
a substantial amount of its loan.
Gota Bank's reconstruction will take place under Sweden's new support
programme for the country's banking system.
