<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 92 / International Company News: General Mills sees record year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MINNEAPOLIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GENERAL MILLS, reporting improved second-quarter returns, expects to achieve
record results for all of fiscal 1993, Reuter reports from Minneapolis.
In a statement, Mr Bruce Atwater, chairman, said he expected another year of
record sales and earnings.
Second-quarter earnings at the leading US consumer foods producer and
restaurateur, rose to Dollars 138.1m, or Dollars 0.85 a share, from Dollars
128.3m, or Dollars 0.76, a year ago. The current-year results included a
gain of Dollars 1.9m, or 1 cent a share, from the sale of the Pycasa frozen
prepared meals business in Spain, and miscellaneous restructuring charges.
The restructuring charges involved the Betty Crocker packaged mixes
production and European food operations. Consumer Foods' operating profits
include a net pre-tax gain from these items of Dollars 19.9m, and corporate
expense includes a Dollars 5.7m charge for the debt call.
Second-quarter sales rose to Dollars 2.1bn from Dollars 1.99bn. Excluding
revenues of Pycasa and the operations that became part of the Snack Ventures
Europe joint venture with PepsiCo Foods International in July, sales rose 10
per cent.
First-half net earnings advanced to Dollars 297.7m, or Dollars 1.82 a share,
from Dollars 270.4m, or Dollars 1.63, previously on revenues of Dollars
4.12bn, up from Dollars 3.91bn.
</TEXT>
